description:
NRCellDU: Table containing configuration parameters for 5G New Radio (NR) Cell DU (Distributed Unit).

- dateTime: Timestamp of the data record.
- Area_Name: Name of the geographical area where the cell is located.
- CellId: Unique identifier for the cell.
- Id2:  Alternative/secondary identifier for the cell.
- Id3: Another alternative identifier for the cell, potentially referencing a different level of granularity.
- vsDataType: Data type identifier, specifying that this is NR Cell DU data.
- vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
- NRCellDU.typeISinglePanelRiRestriction: Restriction on single panel RI type.
- NRCellDU.dftSOfdmPuschStartRsrpThresh: Threshold for DFT-s-OFDM PUSCH start RSRP.
- NRCellDU.ulAvailableCrbs: Available Uplink Carrier Resource Blocks.
- NRCellDU.ailgDlPrbLoadLevel: AILG (Advanced Interference Leveling and Grouping) Downlink PRB load level.
- NRCellDU.drxOnDurationTimer: DRX (Discontinuous Reception) ON duration timer.
- NRCellDU.pdcchOlaSelection: PDCCH (Physical Downlink Control Channel) OLA (Opportunistic Load Adjustment) selection.
- NRCellDU.trsResourceShifting: TRS (Transmit Resource Switching) resource shifting status.
- NRCellDU.ulStartCrb: Uplink start CRB.
- NRCellDU.trsConfigMode: TRS configuration mode.
- NRCellDU.endcDlNrQualHyst: Hysteresis for EN-DC (E-UTRA-NR Dual Connectivity) Downlink NR quality.
- NRCellDU.serviceState: Service state of the cell.
- NRCellDU.sfnOffset: System Frame Number offset.
- NRCellDU.cellBarred: Cell barring status.
- NRCellDU.sNSSAIList: List of S-NSSAI (Single-serving NSSAI).
- NRCellDU.imsEmSupportEnabled: IMS (IP Multimedia Subsystem) Emergency Management support enabled status.
- NRCellDU.networkSignalValue: Network signal value.
- NRCellDU.ailgBeamDirectionEnabled: AILG beam direction enabled status.
- NRCellDU.drxInactivityTimer: DRX inactivity timer.
- NRCellDU.maxUsersRachSchedPusch: Maximum users for RACH (Random Access Channel) scheduled PUSCH.
- NRCellDU.cellReservedForOperator: Cell reservation status for an operator.
- NRCellDU.ulRobustLaEnabled: Uplink Robust Load Adjustment enabled status.
- NRCellDU.nRCellDUId: NR Cell DU ID.
- NRCellDU.drxEnable: DRX enabled status.
- NRCellDU.nrRrpEnabled: NR RRP (Resource Reservation Protocol) enabled status.
- NRCellDU.dlRobustLaEnabled: Downlink Robust Load Adjustment enabled status.
- NRCellDU.pointAArfcnTdd: Point A ARFCN (Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number) TDD.
- NRCellDU.nrLteCoexistence: NR/LTE coexistence enabled status.
- NRCellDU.maxNoOfAdvancedDlMuMimoLayers: Maximum number of advanced DL MU-MIMO layers.
- NRCellDU.pdschRachBoost: PDSCH (Physical Downlink Shared Channel) RACH boost.
- NRCellDU.cbrsCellPriorityRank: CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) cell priority rank.
- NRCellDU.pZeroNomPuschGrant: Nominal power for PUSCH grant.
- NRCellDU.operationalState: Operational state of the cell.
- NRCellDU.pwsBroadcastOngoing: PWS (Power Saving) broadcast ongoing status.
- NRCellDU.endcUlNrLowQualThresh: Threshold for EN-DC Uplink NR low quality.
- NRCellDU.pdcchRachBoost: PDCCH RACH boost.
- NRCellDU.tddBorderVersion: TDD border version.
- NRCellDU.dlAvailableCrbs: Available Downlink Carrier Resource Blocks.
- NRCellDU.tddUlDlPattern: TDD Uplink/Downlink pattern.
- NRCellDU.rachPreambleTransMax: Maximum RACH preamble transmissions.
- NRCellDU.ssbFrequencyAutoSelected: Automatically selected SSB (Synchronization Signal Block) frequency.
- NRCellDU.csiRsConfig4P: CSI-RS (Channel State Information - Reference Signal) configuration for 4 ports.
- NRCellDU.ssbGscn: SSB Global Cell Selection Number.
- NRCellDU.cbrsCellSsbControlEnabled: CBRS cell SSB control enabled status.
- NRCellDU.fixWideBeamsForPeriodicSr: Wide beams fixing for periodic SR (Sounding Reference)
- NRCellDU.nbIotCellDeployed: NB-IoT cell deployment status.
- NRCellDU.pdschStartPrbStrategy: PDSCH start PRB strategy.
- NRCellDU.endcDlNrLowQualThresh: Threshold for EN-DC Downlink NR low quality.
- NRCellDU.nCI: Network Colour Code.
- NRCellDU.nrSrsDlBufferVolThr: NR SRS (Sounding Reference Signal) Downlink buffer volume threshold.
- NRCellDU.ssbDurationAutoSelected: Automatically selected SSB duration.
- NRCellDU.pointAFrequencyTdd: Point A frequency TDD.
- NRCellDU.bfrEnabled: Beamforming Resource enabled status.
- NRCellDU.dlStartCrb: Downlink start CRB.
- NRCellDU.csiReportFormat: CSI report format.
- NRCellDU.rachPreambleRecTargetPower: Target power for received RACH preamble.
- NRCellDU.trsPeriodicity: TRS periodicity.
- NRCellDU.cellResourceMappingRef: Cell resource mapping reference.
- NRCellDU.sibType2: SIB (System Information Block) type 2 information.
- NRCellDU.ulMaxMuMimoLayers: Maximum number of Uplink MU-MIMO layers.
- NRCellDU.csiRsShiftingSecondary: CSI-RS shifting for secondary component.
- NRCellDU.sibType4: SIB type 4 information.
- NRCellDU.nRTAC: NR TAC (Tracking Area Code).
- NRCellDU.ssbOffsetAutoSelected: Automatically selected SSB offset.
- NRCellDU.sibType5: SIB type 5 information.

- NRCellDU.pointAFrequencyUlFdd: Point A frequency Uplink FDD.

- NRCellDU.drxLongCycle: DRX long cycle.
- NRCellDU.puschAllowedInDmrsSym: PUSCH allowed in DMRS (demodulation reference signal) symbols.
- NRCellDU.dlChannelScramblingIdentity: Downlink channel scrambling identity.
- NRCellDU.sibType6: SIB type 6 information.
- NRCellDU.sibType7: SIB type 7 information.
- NRCellDU.sibType8: SIB type 8 information.
- NRCellDU.dl256QamEnabled: Downlink 256-QAM enabled status.

- NRCellDU.srsHoppingBandwidth: SRS hopping bandwidth.

- NRCellDU.pZeroNomSrs: Nominal power for SRS.
- NRCellDU.qRxLevMinOffset: Minimum offset for Q-RxLevMin.

- NRCellDU.trsModeSelected: Selected TRS mode.

- NRCellDU.ulScSpillover: Uplink SC (Subcarrier) spillover.
